<TITLE> Swine flu transmission rate 'falls' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 4 (bdnews24.com)Only 42 new cases of swine flu have been newly detected in the last one week, taking the official tally of people infected with the H1N1 virus in Bangladesh to 646, the IEDCR chief said on Sunday. "Undoubtedly, we can say that the spread of swine flu is easing," said Mahmudur Rahman, director of the Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research. "But we're still ready to fight any situation," he told a weekly briefing. Many countries in Europe and America have started to use the new vaccine; Rahman said this was good news for Bangladesh. "It'll reduce the number of cases around the globe and transmission to our country through travellers. "We're also trying to obtain the vaccine," he added. IEDCR is doing all possible to continue diagnoses despite lower transmission of the virus, he said. The government has so far confirmed three swine flu deaths after the first case was detected on June 18. bdne
